					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Gordon on the gameplay board</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=106281" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
I don't suppose any rogue changes were put in?<P>

<B>Nothing in this patch specifically addressed the rogue class. As far as what we have planned, we're still planning an update for poison, but that's looking to be post-expansion now. Doing a worthwhile update for poison is far more difficult than putting in something like Evade or the hide/sneak/undead thing. It will take a good deal of effort to get it right.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

First of all, what is the reason for making fd only work part of the time, druids get harmonize which works way more than fd<P>

<B>Harmony and Feign Death cannot be compared directly. The spell and skill have two completely different uses. Harmony, for instance, is an outdoor-only offensive spell, and Feign Death is an escape skill that works everywhere.</B><P>

and second will monks be recieving any new skills at lvls 51-60?<P>

<B>All of the melee classes are getting new abilities post-50. Though I wouldn't classify them as skills (a skill being something that you must train up, whereas abilities are semi-innate). We do not, however, wish to comment on any specifics in regards to them at this time.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Congrats Verant, Now Kiting Is Even EASIER!!<P>

Now I can look forward to druids and necros have an even easier time leveling, I was just wondered if anybody else thinks this is too easy for them now!!<P>

<B>*reminds himself that it's impossible to please everyone*<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Can us rogues expect to see comments regarding the poison changes?<P>

<B>Comments as in "When will they be done?" or comments addressing "What will they consist of?" <P>

To the former, we've got it set for post-expansion right now. I posted in another thread about it today:</B>

---SNIP---<BR>
I don't suppose any rogue changes were put in?<P>

<I>Nothing in this patch specifically addressed the rogue class. As far as what we have planned, we're still planning an update for poison, but that's looking to be post-expansion now. Doing a worthwhile update for poison is far more difficult than putting in something like Evade or the hide/sneak/undead thing. It will take a good deal of effort to get it right.</I><BR>
---SNIP---<P>

<B>As for the latter, we're still working on that. All I can say is that it is supposed to be "cool" :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Since harm touch only refreshes about once an hour I think it needs to be unresistable. <P>

<I>Teerog said: All offensive things should be resistable in some fashion, via resists, armor, whatever.</I><P>

<B>We have to agree with Teerog here. Nothing in the game is meant to be a free-ride. LOH can fizzle. HT can be resisted. That is how these things work.</B><P>

Hour and a half, actually.<P>

<B>Oh, and it's 72 minutes.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Why give pet's "slam" the ability to bash without a shild, unless they are ogre, troll, or barb sized?<P>

If this is truly something pet wielders want they should be equiping pets with a shild for god sake.<P>

<B>NPCs (pets included) have always had the ability to bash (slam) without having a shield equipped. The ability was accidently removed in the patch last Friday, and was put back in in the patch today. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Expansion Skills for melee classes...(this one's for you Gordon) What's up with them? Have they already been selected, coded, and finalized (I hope so, release is but a few precious weeks away, but then again... -bah, this isn't a flame, but a qustion) All the casters have their rumored new spells posted on every EQ board from here to Kaladim, but what about the new melee skills?<P>

<B>They've been coded and are currently undergoing balance tests on the Test server. We just aren't ready to release any specific information about them. As for the spell info that's out there, there wasn't much we could do about that. We're just not commenting on them either, and have thrown in a few red herrings to keep people guessing.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

"EMERGENCY PATCH" NEEDS A PATCH!! great job guys. Now you have hundreds of people, myself included, that are having problems even loggin on to the servers. Its not any one in particular, its the same for all.<P>

Also, when you zone, its taking a long long time IF it doesnt just outright drop you!! Anyone care to comment on when we will get another patch to fix this patch? or hell, even just tell us what went wrong!<P>

<B>Yeah, something went awry. It's amazing how some of these issues don't show themselves until we get nearly 50K people in to plug on them at once. <P>

The servers will be coming down again shortly to address this.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

[Note this last post is from Yesterday, not today.]
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
